node.text: ✅One of the best photos😊
@felipelopezart thank you 👍

One of the men who sexually assaulted me is in court today. "Things were *different* then..." (in the 90s) he, and others, have said. Actually, non-consensual penetration has NEVER been OK. The abuse was painful, and being told by my family to keep silent about it, equally so. 
External events in the past year prompted me to take the matter to the police and there's enough 'contemporaneous evidence' for him to be prosecuted. Court isn't an option for everybody who has been abused, but it's crucially important not to bottle up such a degrading experience.

I urge everyone to try and find their voice by whatever means possible. Now that I have broken my silence I am letting out a rush of feeling in my stonecarvings, and find that art is powerful and healing.
(This sculpture was made from a broken kerbstone-- the break is still visible on top. I used the remnant as a base).
Check out @jerrysaltz #33Rules - reading this prompted me to finally get out what I was carrying inside of me #healingart #art #contemporarysculpture #DirectCarving #truthtomaterials #stonesculpture #stone #femaleform #femalefigure #femalespirit #GetYourHandsOffMyBody #HandsUp #MeToo  #reportsexualabuse  #strongwoman #nomeansno #bodypositivity #womanartist #modernsculpture #ukartist #UKsculpture #1001sculptures #sculpture #lucychurchill
@rebecca_wildwood wow Rebecca. I'm so sorry my response came across as such. That's shocked me to the core. I'm so sorry, really I am.

@rebecca_wildwood I'm sorry but I think perhaps you misunderstood Lucy's comment. I think it was an outpouring of appreciation for the other women talking about these issues rather than a "lecture". I'm absolutely certain it wasn't a criticism of what you said in any way x

@phoebejtc But I never said it was criticism to me. I dislike being misinterpreted, so I said so. Lucy’s views were entirely valid, and I support everything Lucy said. But by attaching it to my personal response, I felt it was patronising. That is why I asked if it was necessary. I did not say it was deliberate etc. Considering Lucy knows some of my own awful personal experiences, it was a fair question. However well intentioned, I feel we all have to be mindful of how we address people directly, when we make general points. Me included. But I stand by what I said.
Brave and beautiful work. You are on the vanguard
Stunning work 👌🏼❣👌🏼

@fideslinien thank you so much. So many people have DM'ed me to say #metoo. I'm glad it's opening up the subject but now my head is spinning and I feel washed out today. Being brave and upbeat is exhausting, even though its good...but so I ✨really✨ appreciate your kind words. Xx
@lucychurchillstone It’s your transformation into another level of life! Blessings!!🌞✨✨
@fideslinien yes, that's true.. X

Hi Lucy, I think it’s very brave of you to share this here. To me it seems, Instagram usually is a place for entertainment, happiness and fun. But I believe even serious subjects should be found here. I appreciate and admire how you unveiled this in the context of your beautiful art. Please inspire others with your devotion towards art and I hope you will give hope with what you shared to people who sadly experienced the same. Keep going, Dear!🤸‍♀️➿🤸‍♀️
@emckennadesigns felt brave yesterday, not so much today. Will carve and feel braver tomorrow 👍
Very brave post.  I’m really sorry

@hil_jenner thanks Hilary. I think my brain is braver than my heart or body. I know it to be right so I go forward, but inside I'm curling up 🐁... I would love to meet up, when I've caught my breath xx
@lucychurchillstone definitely up for s catch up - just let me know when you’re free. I’m thinking of you - stay brave ! Xx

Lucy, this is a beautiful sculpture and you are a incredibly brave woman. It must take a lot of courage to take him to court and to write this post. Hopefully, the more women like you that speak about things like this , the sooner society will realise that enough is enough. I am so proud of you. Xx💗
@angiefuz xxxxxx

Oh Lucy- please consider this a great big hug - the carving is phenomenal- I felt its strength before reading your post. Time doesn’t make you forget- I hope you find some solace in creating such a beautiful and powerful piece of art ♥️♥️♥️♥️
@karinamachadoauthor stonecarving is incredibly cathartic!
What a powerful and beautiful piece @lucychurchillstone. In awe of your talent and courage. ❤️
@sellylou_sarah xxxxx💗
I didn’t react immediately but I am proud to follow you on instagram and what you are doing in art and life deepens the perception and courage of others🧡💐💐
@alisonlucy that's the goal for everyone in life isn't it? 🌟 X
@lucychurchillstone yes! You have it. X
@alisonlucy xx
Huge respect to you for finding your power.
Well said, Lucy. Thank you for your huge courage. X
@jammyanj thanks Angela 💛 I hope the inward facing downward hand looks as gentle as the upright is blocking.. 😘
@lucychurchillstone it’s simultaneously strong, yet vulnerable. Like many women. How do you do that. ♥️👏🏼
@jammyanj 😊😘💗💗💗
And by the way, I love this sculpture. X
@jimanekia thanks 💛
Wow

@loutonkin not feeling it at the moment, but thanks. He's pleaded guilty and the sentencing date has been set - and I've collapsed... Just have to keep it together a while longer... Who know what will emerge afterwards?.. 🌼

@lucychurchillstone We don’t know each other but I’m here for you. Considered my shoulder as something you can lean on, cry onto or use to hold you up. You are strong, we are all stronger than we think we are when it comes to it. Have confidence in yourself & support around you xxxx 🌻
@loutonkin ☺😘
You’re amazing xxx

@juanashwort it's very much an intuitive sculpture... I hadn't planned how it would 'look', it just came out that way. In fact, I'd planned the top hand to be inward facing, in a gesture of self reflection. By 'mistake' (?) I flipped the hand round when drawing on... I'd intended to correct this, but overnight realised I needed to sculpt this specific stance. Yay for good old subconscious, eh?! 😄
Also the facelessness just seemed right, once the gesture was in place... X

On the one hand this could be a celebration of the youthfulness of a woman but in the other the blankness of the face and the protectiveness of the hands signify the desperate attempts to absorb trauma. The texture of the stone shows the unnerving rippling.it is like the sacrificial maiden

@juanashwort I used to agonise about 'what to make'! I thought I was institutionalised by making work commemorating other people for so long, or carving anonymously in historic styles... Now I've opened up this sweetie-box of stuff that was always waiting to come out, just surpressed and silenced by the shit like that which is coming to court now 😅
I think your subconscious stuff is great x
@felipelopezart thank you 👍
